3. cs.CO (Combinatorics): The paper deals with partitions, which are a fundamental concept in combinatorics. 
4. cs.GR (Group Theory): The paper deals with the GL_{n^2}(C) group and its representations, which are central to group theory. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): Although less likely, the paper deals with the permanent versus determinant problem, which has applications in control theory and signal processing.
